ad warden}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">49</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Riverfolk :</p>\n<table style=\"width: 634px; height: 66px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 18px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.14nKRAT6nMCMGSUf]{Boatman}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 18px;\">50</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.LaTDWvLySPKGojiW]{Huffer}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">51 - 53</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.EBpCBitHuWElKf3D]{Riverwarden}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">54 - 56</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.wu6aG1XPdzvpiLcR]{Seaman}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">57 - 60</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 441px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.TaOvUqKMJoPeuynD]{Smuggler}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center;\">61</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 441px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.lDvbNLRfv9MsNyf6]{Stevedore}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center;\">62 - 67</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 441px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.AnW8kwDb9koFgMPx]{Wrecker}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center;\">68 - 72</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Rogues :</p>\n<table style=\"width: 634px; height: 66px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 18px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.MY4aFbQL5T9znCUd]{Bawd}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 18px;\">73</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.W2Ovj3ec7eqZUuuv]{Grave Robber}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">74</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.mOljt11dxZENtmoR]{Outlaw}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">75 - 77</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.yGZN7bMjbGH7kCMK]{Racketeer}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">78</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Warriors :</p>\n<table style=\"width: 634px; height: 146px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 18px;\">@Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.journalentries-ok.jIEc62Vs34NCfDXG]{Irongut}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 18px;\">79</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.journalentries-ok.jkIu9G32Ngp9aSvo]{Crusher}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">80 - 90</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.journalentries-ok.VzcSz0fRZNkSh5uO]{Leadbelcher}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">91 - 93</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.qaL8gLZdfOL5F5UV]{Guard}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">94</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.journalentries-ok.NG8L0KRwviEVjSQa]{Mournfang Cavalry}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">95</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.15N8GauWXWfbYbEQ]{Pit Fighter}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">96</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.mlLVNBKIUnonqka2]{Protagonist}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">97</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.career-descriptions.kT0ZI0LoHmIvhjPk]{Soldier}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">98 - 99</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 441px; height: 16px;\">@Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.journalentries-ok.tCcs7k308oloDqEj]{Ogre Butcher}</td>\n<td style=\"width: 188px; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">100</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\n<h3><strong>3. Trappings</strong></h3>\n<p>In Ogre society your gut is what makes you a true Ogre. The fattest are the strongest and most powerful in Ogre society. With the exception of the Butchers, all Ogres wear a Gut-plate as a means to protect their most sacred organs allowing them to consume more in worship to the Great Maw. To see an Ogre&rsquo;s guts ripped out is an even worse fate than death and something all Ogres fear above all else. All Ogre characters, except for Butchers, regardless of Class or Career, always start with a Gut-plate.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><strong>4. Adding Details</strong></h3>\n<p>While you can choose any name that fits the world, here are some hints and tips to help choose one that&rsquo;s right for you. You can also generate a random Ogre name using the Creating Character option in the Actors directy or by clicking the \"Name\" in an ogre NPC sheet.</p>\n<p><strong>Ogre Names:</strong> Greasus, Skrag, Rogurg, Bragh, Ghark, Dargol, Murgog, Vargak, Duzgrut, Kugrok</p>\n<p><strong>Ogre Titles:</strong> The Gutsman, The Slaughterer, Giantbreaker, Mawseeker, Gatecrasher, Goblinjuicer</p>\n<p><strong>Ogre Tribe Names:</strong> Ironsmashers, Bloodgullets, Meatfists, Cragstompers, Steelhulks, Blackhides, Frosttooths</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.0712%; height: 176px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>1D10</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Element One</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Element Two</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\"><strong>Starting Title</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Bra</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">agh</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Big-</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Duz</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">erk</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-Bonesnapper</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Garg</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">gat</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-The Devourer</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Kuz</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">grut</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-The Mountain</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">5</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Murg</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">olg</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\"><strong>*</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">6</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Nog</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">ragh</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-Legbreaker</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">7</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Rog</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">rok</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-Skullsmasher</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">8</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Tar</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">tagh</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-The Feaster</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">9</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Varg</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">thorg</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-The Thug</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">10</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Zeg</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">urg</td>\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">-Trolleater</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>*Use a name related to your current career, as that is what you are best known for in Ogre society&hellip; for now.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Roll a random hair color : @Table[hair]</p>\n<p>Roll a random eye color : @Table[eyes]</p>\n<p>Age : 20+2D10</p>\n<p>Height: 9&rsquo;4&rdquo; + 3d10&rdquo;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Short-term Ogre Ambitions</strong></p>\n<p>Short-term Ambitions represent your immediate goals. They are outcomes you wish to achieve within days and weeks, possibly sooner. Under normal circumstances, a short-term Ambition should take at least two or three sessions to complete.</p>\n<p><strong>Example short-term Ambitions include:</strong></p>\n<p>&bull; Eating your parents.</p>\n<p>&bull; Vowing to eat the killer of a fallen comrade.</p>\n<p>&bull; Building a shrine to the Great Maw and offering it fresh meat.</p>\n<p><strong>Long-term Ogre Ambitions</strong></p>\n<p>Long-term Ambitions are goals you will need to work on for months or years to complete, and may never be achieved at all, perhaps taken more as a description of a primary motivation in your life than a realistic outcome.</p>\n<p><strong>Examples of long-term Ambitions include:</strong></p>\n<p>&bull; Owning your own Maneater mercenary company.</p>\n<p>&bull; Consuming an Enormous or Monstrous sized creature.</p>\n<p>&bull; Bringing a massive and exotic offering to the Great Maw in the Dark Lands.</p>\n<p>&bull; Taking over your tribe by eating the previous Ogre Tyrant.</p>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: center;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>Mutation Table</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: center;\">1 - 80</td>\n<td style=\"width: 70%; text-align: center;\">Physical</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: center;\">81 - 100</td>\n<td style=\"width: 70%; text-align: center;\">Mental</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><strong>5. Ogre Legendary Tribe Traits</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Goldtooth Tribe:</strong> The wealthiest and most powerful Ogre tribe in the world. Lead by Overtyrant Greasus Goldtooth, the Goldtooth tribe houses the largest number of ironguts wearing armor encrusted with gems and precious metals due to their sheer amount of wealth and power.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&bull; You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.OROfMcVqRnZHINkU]{Wealthy} Talent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Thunderguts Tribe:</strong> The most extortive and exploitative of the Ogre tribes. They are known to capture entire towns and villages, and even orc strongholds, holding them to ransom&mdash;often leveling them to dust and double-crossing once paid.</p>\n<p>&bull; You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing} Talent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Crossed Clubs:</strong> The most warlike of the Ogre tribes and the one that fields the most Maneaters. Their abundance of hard fighting mercenaries and veterans is second only to their wide collection of outlandish wargear, wearing turbans from Araby, wielding clubs from the Badlands or lizard skull helmets from the Southlands.</p>\n<p>&bull; You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.zGQ0ShUTSlUvVtWh]{Warrior Born} Talent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>The Sons of the Mountain:</strong> The best hunters of the Ogre tribes. They are known to hunt the most dangerous and titanic of beasts.</p>\n<p>&bull; You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.bxbTiLzbaz4vdukT]{Hunter's Eye} Talent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Feastmaster Tribe:</strong> The most well-fed of the Ogre tribes known to eat the best quality food second only to the Goldtooths. They are known for their abundance of halfling cooks&mdash;not of their own will for fear of being &ldquo;in the trough&rdquo; and being a Ogres next meal.</p>\n<p>&bull; You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Halflings)} Talent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Rock Skulls:</strong> The toughest of the Ogre tribes. They are known for their boulder-butting contests, splitting rocks with their thick skulls. They are notoriously dim-witted.</p>\n<p>&bull; You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.FF41XPboORgyDNsv]{Strong Back} Talent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Blood Guzzlers:</strong> The renown hunters and eaters of giant spiders in the Vale of Webs. They are known to be the best experts at hunting spiders in the Dark Lands, so much that they&rsquo;ve built a tolerance to the many venoms inflicted on them by their prey.</p>\n<p>&bull; You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.vMYEkrWj0ip6ZOdv]{Resistance (Poison)} Talent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Ironskin Tribe:</strong> The fiercest and most hard-hitting of the Ogre tribes. They are known for their black iron gut-plates and devastating charges believed to be unstoppable even by rival tribes. They are notorious for grabbing as many slaves during a battle as possible to sell them to the Chaos Dwarfs of Zharr Naggrund.</p>\n<p>&bull; You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.oRx92ByVNEBN6YkK]{Berserk Charge} Talent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>The Lazarghs:</strong> One of the oldest and most feared of the Ogre tribes and descendants of the first prophet of the Maw. They live in the hellish, warp radiated wind-swept wastes of the southern Ancient Giant Lands and are known to be twisted and heavily deformed due to their harsh living conditions.</p>\n<p>&bull; You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.jviOQmy0luQOySC2]{Tenacious} Talent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Mountaineaters Tribe:</strong> The tribe made famous by Bauldig Moutaineater, this tribe is known for their ability to eat rocks for nourishment in the name of their charismatic and powerful leader. They prefer eating subterranean races such as Dwarfs, Skaven and Greenskins above all else.</p>\n<p>&bull; You gain the @Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.talents-ok.2K8fUf6RhkfZKAzB]{Iron Gut} Talent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Eyebiter Tribe:</strong> The most infamous tribe of the ivory, Silver and Spice roads, raiding and enslaving the many traders from the Old World to Cathay and Ind. They are known for their fast raids, ambushing and charging caravans before they have anytime to react and leaving before any mercenaries, guards or other Ogre tribes can catch up to them.</p>\n<p>&bull; You gain the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.AwUUEwwf2Vt4ksCN]{Sprinter} Talent.</p>"}
{"_id":"NqzpYgmiNBQ5EEIe","name":"Firebelly","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.tgrwQjsHu30zc6um"}},"content":"<p>&ldquo;Firebellies are the roaring, blazing priests of the Ogre deity known as the Fire Mouth. Quick to mirth and anger alike, Firebellies are garrulous and vital individuals who are readily welcomed into any Ogre tribe. Fire burns within these larger-than-life prophets in a literal as well as metaphorical sense.</p>\n<p>The Fire Mouth is the largest and most powerful volcano in the Mountains of Mourn. It is an important figure in Ogre mythology, revered alongside the Great Maw by all Ogres and worshiped fervently by those tribes that have witnessed the violence of its mighty eruptions firsthand. Every year, dozens of Ogre pilgrims flock to the sides of the Fire Mouth and announce their presence to the small but influential tribe that makes its home in caves nestled into the volcano slopes. As magma courses down the sides of the Fire Mouth like drool from a Butcher's gob, the aspirants dare to undergo the gruelling Flame Trial -- a mysterious ritual held by the Firebelly tribe as their volcano god rumbles in his sleep.</p>\n<p>As will all other religious occasions in the Ogre Kingdoms, this trial by fire begins and end with the act of ingesting something. First, the hopeful Ogre must gobble down an entire cauldron full of flametoad and devilpepper curry; a repugnant mixture also useful for ending protracted sieges. Even as his gut burns, he must then catch one of the carthorse-sized fire beetles that burrow through the lava streams and devour the critter in a single sitting. It is the final task, however, that is deadliest of all.</p>\n<p>Before being accepted and becoming a Firebelly, the aspirant must drink the blood of the Fire Mouth. The supplement first climbs atop the caldera of the titanic volcano. The sight of the lake of bubbling, hissing magma below is impressive enough to take the breath away, even before the sulpherous stench assails the nostrils. Many contenders flee at this point, but those with the courage to continue are slowly lowered on thick chains inside the mouth of the volcano. The heat is such that their hair is burnt from their bodies and their eyes boil in their sockets, but the truly faithful will persevere, scooping up a skull-full of roiling lava. After being hauled back up to the edge of the Fire Mouth, the Ogre must gulp the molten rock down in a single draught. This last act is lethal even for the most gastronomically inviolable Ogre; only those with the blessing of the volcano god can survive.</p>\n<p>The survival and subsequent initiation of a new Firebelly happens perhaps a few times every decade, and often coincides with a major outburst of flame from the Fire Mouth itself. This is seen as a sure signal that it is time to make war on the lands of the weak, with the size of the battles to come coinciding with the strength of the eruption. In war, the Firebellies are well equipped to aid the Ogres, for the disciples of the volcano inherit supernatural powers. Firebellies bear a measure of protection against the fiercest conflagrations, can breathe out an inferno upon their foes and can even cast and control flaming spells.</p>\n<p>The Fire Mouth has only a few priests on hand at any time, for they are never many and most of their kind journey alone into the Ogre Kingdoms. There, a Firebelly will join a tribe for a time, spreading the creed of their molten-hearted god and bringing fiery destruction to their foes. They are lively and popular transients and fill Ogres full of wonder with their ability to bleed magma and cause a wreath of flames about their bodies with each burst of explosive flatulence.&rdquo;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>&mdash;Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Ogre</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Academics</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Firebelly Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 640px; height: 34px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">IV</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">II</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">III</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>I. @Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.careers-ok.IwqUGJ33QNJ6lAdf]{Firegut}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.gh91jaxzTBgbMoi5]{Channelling (Aqshy)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)}, @Compendium[wfrp