>, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.bBLK2hznjPlby6Jb]{Play (Drums)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.J9MK0AIaTbvd5oF6]{Drilled}, @Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.talents-ok.2K8fUf6RhkfZKAzB]{Iron Gut}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.qZ4cFy6z482ZONuA]{Sturdy}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.RmY0CUjiFYZ3GEKY]{Very Resilient}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Buckler, Chain Coat<br /><br /></p>\n<h3><strong>II. @Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.careers-ok.lOqBBGAbRrsPILns]{Irongut}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.7pQo66cESWttzIlb]{Gamble}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.nLlRDNRC95plBgXs]{Lore (Metallurgy)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Ml6ZblglcSbVhXyh]{Trade (Smith)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.wrpVYmdiIy1jPulc]{Break and Enter}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.oRx92ByVNEBN6YkK]{Berserk Charge}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.JLzJws09GMw9GWBV]{Coolheaded}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.zGQ0ShUTSlUvVtWh]{Warrior Born}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Plate Armor and Helm, Shield<br /><br /></p>\n<h3><strong>III. @Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.careers-ok.gesPgEMy2PM7ECII]{Irongut Champion}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.HXZaV1CJhmTvcAz4]{Heal}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.os4NKy5Oy6sRt1eh]{Outdoor Survival}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.HO8vIjGTHjmenIaV]{Perform (Fighting)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.BlHVzfs0Ow6IYEDw]{Furious Assault}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.GHmXS9zGNx3PWYZc]{Master Tradesman (Smith)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.nWLsoWQBCjPRKxYx]{Robust}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.4MJJCiOKPkBByYwW]{Strike Mighty Blow}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Quality Melee Weapon (Any)<br /><br /></p>\n<h3><strong>IV. @Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.careers-ok.GiRolLr6HcQVc0X2]{Gutlord}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Warfare)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.GU1KpgY3MeFIaDaq]{Careful Strike}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.GRRN3XAKIpEVCY7z]{Craftsman (Smith)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.uRvOg8AnCcP2ufx8]{Resolute}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.vCgEAetBMngR53aT]{War Leader}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Quality Smith Tools, Unit of Ironguts</p>"}
{"name":"Crusher","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.FUthwicZHW8UBxQa"}},"content":"<p>&ldquo;Ogre Bulls is a term used to describe all the fighting-age, adult male Ogres within a tribal kingdom or society, an unwashed mass of muscle and fat that can flatten landscapes as well as towns and villages when they gather in horrificly large numbers. Big, brutish and extremely violent, Ogre Bulls are simple and straightforward creatures; they know what they want and use their brawn to take it.</p>\n<p>Most Bulls don't do contemplative head scratching, preferring to smash things they don't understand. The straightforward bull-charge is their favored way to smash any opposition and greedily grab what they like. And what Ogres want is power, respect, wealth and, perhaps most of all, an endless supply of meat to feast upon. It is the Ogre way to take more than their share, in fact, most Bulls have a bully mentality that pushes them to take as much as possible. The only way to stop their aggression is a show of superior force even greater than them.</p>\n<p>Ogre Bruisers usually act as enforcers or under-chieftains within their tribal kingdom, and they spend a great deal of their time smashing and pummeling in the name of their Tyrant. As a payment for using their fighting skills and brawn, Bruisers have many privileges in the tribe. Not least of these is the license to smack seven shades of dung out of any Ogre not toeing the line, not eating messily enough, or spending too much time playing with his Gnoblars.</p>\n<p>This bullying behaviour doesn't make them popular with the rest of the tribe, though most Ogres have learnt that it's better to keep their mouths shut -- at least while the Bruiser is within hearing distance, anyway. Occasionally an Ogre will fight back, and in the unlikely event that he wins the resulting brawl, he will be allowed to take the Bruiser's place. This right of challenge serves to keep the Bruisers in line and ensures that they don't take too much advantage of their privileged position.</p>\n<p>A Bruiser is second only to the Tyrant in terms of pure size and strength and is often related to the Kingdom's ruler by blood relations. Comparable to the chieftain of an Ogre tribe, it is the Bruisers who generally keep order and disicipline within the ranks of the tribes when the Tyrant's eye is elsewhere. They are physically massive and are generally the champions of the Ogre games that play such a large part of their culture and society.</p>\n<p>Ogre Tyrants are the ruthless and tyrannical rulers of the tribal kingdoms that dot the slopes and valleys of the Mountains of Mourn. Ogres call the leaders of their tribes Tyrants and it is easy to see why. Tyrants are the biggest and strongest individuals in a hulking race that prides itself on these very same physical and mental features. To claim rulership over a group of Ogres, and even an entire tribal kingdom requires a mighty brawler, a creature powerful enough to wrestle a Giant to the ground or smash his way through a fortified gate using only his bare fists and his own raw rage and determination. This is what a Tyrant has to embody to both his enemies and his allies alike. An Ogre Tyrant uses his tremendous size and brawn to dominate all before him, earning him the right to command the tribe by displaying prodigious feats of what the Ogres respect the most -- strength, violence, extraordinary girth and a healthy, all-consuming appetite that knows no bounds.&rdquo;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>&mdash;Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Ogre</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Warrior</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Crusher Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 640px; height: 34px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">II</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">III</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">IV</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>I. @Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.careers-ok.NHNAJlTqSKBoIlLw]{Ogre Bull}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.d3VZwO4Y5JH5DXdT]{Bribery}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.7pQo66cESWttzIlb]{Gamble}, <em>@Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}</em>, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Local)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.jLyoyqwmBVPjRjhM]{Melee (Brawling)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.HO8vIjGTHjmenIaV]{Perform (Fighting)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.2Nzqsc9aclP6rpnl]{Dirty Fighting}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.Zf0vk2rjllpDh0Ua]{Very Strong}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.zGQ0ShUTSlUvVtWh]{Warrior Born}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Tribe Markings, d10 Ogre Rations<br /><br /></p>\n<h3><strong>II. @Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.careers-ok.0JVs3SuoYyoorDCR]{Ogre Crusher}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.sRuMlaPU5xdIrwhd]{Climb}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.nqhgjUbJWglxU59j]{Language (Battle Tongue)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Lst4xxUcxTYMlD3U]{Melee (Two-Handed)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.zZUX7wO4rOo8k9F0]{Navigation}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.oRx92ByVNEBN6YkK]{Berserk Charge}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.xx8SgdWYEjKct7ym]{Implacable}, @Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.talents-ok.yhhDCCoohUcBcjVI]{Maw Chomp}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.SgjJMBgc85aswvhm]{Relentless}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Personal Gnoblar or Halfling, Melee Weapon (Any)</p>\n<h3><strong>III. @Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.careers-ok.VtRcufJu4WPkpG1C]{Ogre Bruiser}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Warfare)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.PzimjNx9Ojq4g6mV]{Melee (Polearm)}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.hXcfygzujgyMN1uI]{Frenzy}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.mqo51ORnxijcqNNu]{Frightening}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.BlHVzfs0Ow6IYEDw]{Furious Assault}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Quality Gut Plate, Melee Weapon (Any)</p>\n<h3><strong>IV. @Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.careers-ok.Kc1vcbbBDWzy4ayB]{Ogre Tyrant}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 7<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.x8g3U68oi8XzWiYr]{Commanding Presence}, @Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.talents-ok.ZBtwnMacIJYAnr0R]{Extreme Girth}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.zImcTgEl2XNnbu5W]{Hardy}, @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.vCgEAetBMngR53aT]{War Leader}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Best Quality Gut-plate, Large Unit of Gnoblar Slaves, Unit of Ogre Bulls, Small Unit of Bruisers, Your Own Ogre Tribe, Quality Melee Weapon (Any)</p>","_id":"jkIu9G32Ngp9aSvo"}
{"_id":"qqdjmuCjgHYsuF3S","name":"Playing and GMing an Ogre character","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.Zt9ufKaecdAQtEBc"}},"content":"<ol>\n<li>\n<h4><strong>Size Large Optional Rules &amp; Balancing</strong></h4>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h4><strong>Ogre Culture &amp; Status</strong></h4>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h4><strong>Ogre Hunger</strong></h4>\n</li>\n<li>\n<h4><strong>Opinions</strong></h4>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2><strong>1. Size Large Optional Rules &amp; Balancing</strong></h2>\n<p>WFRP is a very customizable game experience. Much like the core game, if the GM feels there is something wrong with how the careers are designed, talents are placed, stats are rolled, then it is highly encouraged to change the rules to facilitate a better experience for everyone. However, balance is still a contentious subject to many GM&rsquo;s, so here are some optional rules to help mitigate concerns regarding @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.8slW8CJ2oVTxeQ6q]{Size Large} PC&rsquo;s. For a full list of effects regarding Size Large Creatures, refer to page 341 of the Warhammer Fantasy Roleplay 4E Core Book.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Limit the Wounds to (SB + 2xTB) x 2, ignoring Willpower bonus for Wounds for Size Large PCs.</li>\n<li>Remove the Damaging Quality that Size Large PCs would gain for being one step larger than a Size Average creature.</li>\n<li>Remove the Deathblow rule gained for successfully striking Size Average targets as a Size Large PC.</li>\n<li>Do not have Size Average creatures automatically gain the @Condition[Fear] Condition during an encounter against the Size Large PC.</li>\n<li>Do not allow the Size Large PC to ignore the need to Disengage if it wishes to leave melee combat against Size Average creatures; instead, have them follow the standard rules for Disengagement.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\n<h3><strong>Size Large Pros and Cons</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong> Regardless of what combination of optional rules are used to balance play for Size Large PCs it is recommended to still grant them some of the advantages for being a Size Large creature against Size Average opponents.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Grant them the advantage they gain in Opposed Strength Tests (and similar) against smaller creatures. It is also recommended to grant Size Large PCs a bonus for certain Strength Tests over Size Average creatures, perhaps in additional SLs, removing penalties or adding bonuses as determined by the GM. Granting them a +20 for a Strength Test that would normally be a Challenging (+0) Test for a smaller creature is a good example. This can also apply to @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidation} Tests. A bandit is much more likely to be scared off by an ogre than your average dwarf, elf, halfling or human.</li>\n<li>Allow the &ndash;2 SL penalty for opponents when they use Melee to defend in an Opposed Test for each step larger the Size Large PC is over them.</li>\n<li>Size Large PCs can use the Stomp ability against smaller creatures and have access to the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.pLW9SVX0TVTYPiPv]{Bite} Trait.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong> Regardless of what combination of optional rules are used to balance play for Size Large PCs it is still important to remember the disadvantages for being a Size Large creature against Size Average opponents.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A smaller creature gains a bonus of +10 for WS to hit.</li>\n<li>Size Large creatures grant a +20 Combat Difficulty Modifier for all Ballistic Skill tests if shot at for being a bigger target.</li>\n<li>Harsher penalties could be inflicted towards stealth due to the mass of the Size Large creature; however, stealth should still be a possibility. It is the GMs discretion for how to handle @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.McTtmZu3Ac8Lh48W]{Stealth} Tests.</li>\n<li>Wagons and carts meant for smaller species such as humans and dwarfs could be much harder to house Size Large creatures, possibly inflicting penalties to Drive Tests due to their sheer weight. This includes lodgings at Inns, doorways, restaurants, caves, shops and other similar facilities and services, unless they are designed or specified otherwise.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>These are just a few examples GMs can think of to make campaigns with Size Large PCs more immersive.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2><strong>2. Ogre Culture &amp; Status</strong></h2>\n<p>Status for Ogres operates the same as it does within the Core Book, pages 49-50. However, amongst Ogres, status is more than just fancy titles and money. Might Makes Right in Ogre society and only the fattest and the strongest are worthy of respect.</p>\n<p>The fattest Ogres hold a special status within their twisted hierarchy. Those with the biggest guts are feared as much as they are respected, their raw strength easily shown on display whenever challenged by other Ogres or warlords of different species. A fatter Ogre&rsquo;s Status is considered one Tier higher when speaking with skinnier Ogres and cannot be defied in Ogre society. An Ogre&rsquo;s fatness is determined by their Toughness Bonus. Ogre&rsquo;s with a higher Toughness Bonus that confront Ogre&rsquo;s with a lower Toughness Bonus gain the benefits of having a higher Status over the other for social Tests. If the Toughness Bonuses are the same, compare Toughness Characteristics and see which is higher, and if those are the same then both Ogres are treated as equals. This effect does not apply to non-Ogre races such as Dwarfs, Elves, Halflings and Humans.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2><strong>3. Ogre Hunger</strong></h2>\n<p>Like all creatures, Ogres need food to survive; however, due to their physiology and the fact their culture is built entirely around mass consumption it is much more vital for Ogres to eat regularly and in mass quantities more so than any other species.</p>\n<p>Every day without food requires a <strong>Hard (-10) @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance} Test</strong>. The first failed Tests causes a penalty of &ndash;10 Strength and Toughness and the Ogre gains the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.xneBqGOs1QS7kfUr]{Hungry} Trait. Second and subsequent failures reduce all other Characteristics by &ndash;10 and cause 2d10+TB Damage not modified by Armor Points. If the Ogre goes more than 3 days without eating, it gains the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.psychologies.DrNUTPeodEgpWTnT]{Frenzy} Psychology and will attempt to kill and consume the nearest creature within its sight&mdash;including its allies, regardless of species.</p>\n<p>The Ogre must consume at least its weight in food every day, with the amount equal to quadruple its Encumbrance unmodified by Talents or Trappings. If the Ogre eats beyond the required amount, it satisfies its endless hunger for an additional day every time it consumes its weight in food.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><strong>Ogre Food Trappings</strong></h3>\n<p>Ogre equivalents of food items listed in the Core Book do exist with Ogre tribes, camps and outposts making and selling their own equivalent of rations and daily food supplies. These foods are much rarer to find as they are only purchasable from other Ogres, are completely inedible to other species and cost double the regular price for food trappings; however, Ogre food trapping are much more filling and can satisfy an Ogre&rsquo;s food requirement for one day.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><strong>Edible Creatures</strong></h3>\n<p>There is no creature the Ogres cannot eat. Every species and race of the forces of Order, Destruction and Chaos are edible to the Ogres due to their unnaturally powerful stomach acids and high resistance to mutations. From undead skeletons, zombies and vampires to even plague daemons of Nurgle. There is literally no creature an Ogre isn&rsquo;t capable of eating. Ogres suffer no penalties, conditions, sicknesses or symptoms for consuming creatures of any kind, regardless of Creature Traits. If an Ogre consumes a creature with the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.traits.xsGbDFqK2qh7lsIj]{Corruption} Trait then it must roll an @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance} Test, with Difficulty Modifiers as determined by the GM, or gain Corruption Points equal to its Rating. This does not make Ogres immune to poisons or disease, but the consumption of such creatures has no effect.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><strong>Cooking Tests</strong></h3>\n<p>Ogres are the most infamous cooks on the entire planet, butchering and consuming any species you can imagine. Their cooking techniques stretch back thousands of years: From Dwarf &amp; Potato Stew, to Greenskin Kebabs and Halfling Dumplings. Cooking and seasoning food using the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.epSHxgJWtT1S0yMY]{Trade (Cook)} Skill makes for much more appetizing and filling meals. For every +SL during a @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.epSHxgJWtT1S0yMY]{Trade (Cook)} Test you increase the Encumbrance of the food being consumed by the Ogre.</p>\n<p><strong>Example:</strong><em> &ldquo;Glug Brewbelly is hauling back the corpses of a few Orcs he recently killed for his famous &lsquo;Orc Skin Soup&rsquo;. Glug throws the Orc corpses into the pot and starts cooking using his Trade (Cook) Skill. Glug scores +3 SL and makes himself and his fellow Maneaters a piping hot bowl of soup that fills each of them up for 13 Encumbrance worth of hunger instead of the 10 Encumbrances it would have normally filled.&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><strong>Recipes</strong></h3>\n<p>What&rsquo;s cooking without some style? Recipes are a method of cooking Ogres can use to help greatly boost their prominence and prestige amongst other Ogres. Creating Recipes also adds bonuses for @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.epSHxgJWtT1S0yMY]{Trade (Cook)} Tests, as keeping track of all the necessary ingredients such as meats, herbs and spices makes it much easier to prepare future meals. The more Recipes you create and the more diverse meals you make, the more other Ogres will flock to you and pay handsomely for your quality cooking. Recipes can also be researched from Cookbooks with Ogres selling their own Recipes for large sums of GC to the highest bidder&mdash;often a Tyrant for his Butchers or Halfling cooks to make. If you have the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Recipes)} Skill you can identify the Recipes of various Ogres, Halflings and other species just based off the ingredients alone. To create a Recipe the Ogre, or someone they know who will help, will need the @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write} Talent and to follow the requirements below:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Name:</strong> Your Recipe&rsquo;s Name.</p>\n<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong> You need one or more meats of any species and the amount you require for the Recipe.</p>\n<p><strong>Seasonings:</strong> Extra ingredients that add a special flavor to your dish including things such as mixed spices, herbs or liquor.</p>\n<p><strong>Cooking Utensils:</strong> The tools you will need to create the Recipe, such as a cauldron for stews, grills for steaks, or pots and pans for eggs &amp; bacon.</p>\n<p><strong>Time:</strong> The cooking time it takes for your Recipe to be created. This portion is varied and depending on the food type can take anywhere from a few minutes to several hours.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>The more detail you add to the Recipe the higher the bonus should be. Example:</strong><em> &ldquo;Glug Brewbelly is hauling back the corpses of a few Orcs he recently killed for his famous &lsquo;Orc Skin Soup&rsquo;. Glug throws the Orc corpses into the pot and starts cooking using his @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.epSHxgJWtT1S0yMY]{Trade (Cook)} Skill. Using his Recipe, he adds various spices imported from Araby, fresh picked herbs he recently purchased from the market and some recently collected Beastmen tongues and eyes for good measure. For following his Recipe and utilizing a wide array of ingredients Glug receives a +40 Difficulty Modifier to his @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.epSHxgJWtT1S0yMY]{Trade (Cook)} Skill Test.&rdquo;</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><strong>Cooking and Eating Endeavors</strong></h3>\n<p>Between adventures, all Ogre characters must undertake one Endeavour managing their hunger, seeing to that they&rsquo;re well fed and comfortably living off the land they occupy. Ogres commonly host eating and cooking competitions with each other during this time. They&rsquo;re often decent sized gatherings to see who can out-eat or out-cook the other Ogres the fastest and messiest ways possible. The winner gets to enjoy the self-satisfaction of having eaten an Ogre&rsquo;s feast worth of food&hellip; and possibly a little money if they bet on the side. To perform in these activities the Ogre rolls Opposed Endurance, for eating, and @Compendium[wfrp4e-core.skills.epSHxgJWtT1S0yMY]{Trade (Cook)} Skill Tests.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><strong>Favorite Snack</strong></h3>\n<p>All Ogres have their favorite foods and will do anything to get another taste. Every Ogre gets the @Compendium[ogre-kingdom-wfrp4e.talents-ok.lRzoGVuZzWsh70DU]{Favorite Snack (Target)} Psychology. Pick one species your Ogre craves the most. When confronting that species, they are immune to Intimidation and Fear from it and will target it first above all other opponents until it&rsquo;s dead. <strong>Species include:</strong> Beastmen, Greenskins, Halflings, Skaven, etc.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2><strong>4. Opinions</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>On Reiklander Humans&hellip;</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;Boney and not enough meat on them&hellip; but there&rsquo;s a lot of &lsquo;em&hellip; and they pay good. I say work fer &lsquo;em, eat &lsquo;em if you like but there&rsquo;s better eatin&rsquo; elsewhere. If you&rsquo;re workin&rsquo; for &lsquo;em, that still means good eatin&rsquo;. Them Imperials got a lot of enemies that need killin&rsquo;&hellip;&rdquo;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&mdash;Golgfag Maneater, Legendary Ogre Maneater</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>On Dwarfs&hellip;</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;They are hard, tough and stubborn&mdash;like rocks! It&rsquo;s just as much of a pain workin&rsquo; for &lsquo;em as eatin&rsquo; &lsquo;em&hellip; they stay put in their holds, behind big doors&hellip; if you do break in, and eat just a few of &lsquo;em, they get angry and send armies or those red headed guys with the tattoos&hellip; they taste good, but they aint worth the trouble&hellip;&rdquo;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&mdash;Golgfag Maneater, Legendary Ogre Maneater</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>On Halflings&hellip;</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;Delicious! The best meal and I don&rsquo;t wanna hear otherwise! The shorties is good eatin&rsquo;&hellip; when they aint bein&rsquo; eatin&rsquo; they are the best cooks money can buy. Easier to have &lsquo;em around cookin&rsquo; for yah than chasen&rsquo; &lsquo;em down&hellip;&rdquo;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&mdash;Golgfag Maneater, Legendary Ogre Maneater</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>On High Elves&hellip;</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;Stringy, with a rich aftertaste. They make for good business&hellip; trade is easy&hellip; they pay me good coin to cross the mountains. Their wine is the best&hellip; they&rsquo;re too rare to cook with&hellip; better to stick with business&mdash;but if they don&rsquo;t pay&hellip; they make a fine desert&hellip;&rdquo;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&mdash;Greasus Goldtooth, Overtyrant and leader of the Goldtooth Tribe</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>On Wood Elves&hellip;</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;Worst job of my life&hellip; they used us&hellip; buttered us up with a feast, wine and gold&hellip; then they sent us into an army of Skaven instead of the Empire... Never again. I aint ever going near Athel Loren&hellip; don&rsquo;t care how much they pay me&hellip;&rdquo;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&mdash;Braggat Rockjaw, Stonegut Mercenary Captain</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>On Gnomes&hellip;</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;What in the Maw&rsquo;s name is a &lsquo;gnome&rsquo;?&rdquo;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&mdash;Anonymous Ogre Mercenary</p>"}
{"name":"Ogre Butcher","permission":{"default":0,"lNumE4kwYfzQkIkY":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.p3ri2wu94eVVkUou"}},"content":"<p>&ldquo;Ogre Butchers are second only to Tyrants in terms of power and influence, for they not only the spiritual and magical representative of their tribe and god, but they are also the tribe's foremost cooks. Through the gory ritual preparation and consumption of meat, Butchers channel a portion of their fearsome deity's eternal hunger into feats of magic. Invoking the single-minded strength of their god, Butchers can instill unnatural vitality to their comrades, swelling the Ogres muscles and toughening their skin. They can even turn their wrath upon the enemy, causing bones to break or the ground to open up and swallow their foes.</p>\n<p>Although not as mighty as a Tyrant, a Butcher is an emissary of the Great Maw and is held in both awe and fear by his tribe. Butchers prepare all of a tribe's feasts, celebrations in which all Ogres take great pride. Around camp a Butcher is given a wide berth, for it is best not to get too close in case he is looking for extra ingredients, as fingers or whole limbs have been known to go missing. In battle, however, Butchers are most often found right in the thick of the fighting, where they use their cleavers and magic to great effect.</p>\n<p>Butchers are typically more rotund than an average Ogre and have even worse personal hygiene. They often resemble walking larders, for in addition to being caked in dried blood and offal, Butchers adorn themselves in chunks of meat, along with an array of meat hooks, cleavers, filleting knives and even special tenderisers tucked into a leather apron, or even pierced through their flabby skin. A Butcher must be prepared to use these items in their gore-soaked rituals at a moment's notice. Of all true Ogres, only the Butchers do not wear a gut-plate -- they trust their guts to the protection of the Great Maw.</p>\n<p>Any infant that conforms to the recognised portents is immediately handed to the tribe's Butcher, who bites deep into the whelp's gut to claim it as his own. The Butcher then force-feeds the child in a continual glut until the proteg&eacute; has grown fat and strong. Further initiations into the secrets of the Great Maw include gulping down rotten meat and toxins to build a tolerance to poison, learning the art of grinding bones to meal, and discovering which parts of a beast to devour to augment different magics.</p>\n<p>Butchers are responsible for blessing their tribal warriors with the power of the Great Maw itself, as well as inflicting great harm to those that dare to stand before them. Some Butchers show an inclination towards magics other than the Great Maw. Some take powers from the very animals they cull, while those who dream of an oncoming fiery comet have a penchant for reading the future and controlling the weather in destructive ways, whilst always looking to the heavens for some sky-borne disaster. Still other Butchers revel in the final act of their killing work, and their spells focus on death and dying. Regardless of their focus, Ogres believe that to cross a Butcher is to cross the Great Maw itself, a certain recipe for a painful doom.&rdquo;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><strong>&mdash;Warhammer Wiki</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Species:&nbsp;</strong>Ogre</p>\n<p><strong>Class:&nbsp;</strong>Warrior</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Butcher Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"width: 640px; height: 34px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px; text-align: center;\">S</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">T</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: center;\">I</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 61px; text-align: c